<head>SHUT</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>CLOSE</item>
<item>PULL/PUSH TO</item>
<item>SLAM</item>
<item>FASTEN</item>
<item>PUT THE LID ON</item>
<item>BAR</item>
<item>LOCK</item>
<item>SECURE</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">關閉</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">閉</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BLOCK a DOOR OR A GATE in an ORDINARY WAY.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most general word for closing anything is probably bì 閉.</p>
<p>2. Guān 關 refers specifically to shut and lock a door with a bolt.</p>
<p>3. Jiǒng 扃 refers to closing and locking a door from the outside.</p>
<p>4. Hé 闔 is an archaic and dignified word for closing something, mostly a door.</p>
<p>5. Mán 瞞 refers occassionally to closing one's eyes.</p>
<p>6. Fēng 封 can refer to closing and sealing something.</p>
        </div>
